# Fix: Eliminate Reseed/Shed Churn in STOP Band

## Context

After deploying STOP-band entry shedding and guarding Step 6c's reseed path, production logs still show a reseedâ†’shed cycle every ~30-70s. The bot places ~47 entry orders, then immediately sheds them next loop when STOP band triggers again. This wastes API calls and creates unnecessary Kraken rate-limit pressure.

**Root cause**: There are 3 reseed code paths in `main.py`. Only Path 3 (Step 6c) was guarded. The other two still reseed entries during STOP band, and the capacity band oscillates (entries placed â†’ over threshold â†’ STOP â†’ shed â†’ under threshold â†’ non-STOP â†’ reseed â†’ repeat).

